Model Evaluation Function¶

In [19]:
def model_eval(model, X, Y, seed=1, flag=0):
    
    rs = RobustScaler()
    X = pd.DataFrame(rs.fit_transform(X), columns=X.columns)
    
    xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(X, Y, train_size=0.8, random_state = seed)
    
    model.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
    trainpred = model.predict(xtrain)
    testpred = model.predict(xtest)
    
    if flag:
        check_assumption(model, xtrain, ytrain, trainpred)
    
    print("Training the model...\n")
    print("Train RMSE :", np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(ytrain, trainpred)) )
    print("Train R2 :", r2_score(ytrain, trainpred) )
    print("\nTest RMSE :", np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(ytest, testpred)) )
    print("Test R2 :", r2_score(ytest, testpred) )
    try:
        coeff = pd.DataFrame({'Col':X.columns, 'Coeff':model.coef_})
    except:
        coeff = pd.DataFrame({'Col':X.columns, 'Coeff':model.feature_importances_})
    
    coeff = coeff.sort_values('Coeff', ascending=True)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 5))
    plt.bar(coeff.Col, coeff.Coeff)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()

Assumption Testing¶

In [20]:
def check_assumption(model, x, y, pred, los= 0.05):
    print("Checking model assumptions...")
    
    residuals = y - pred
    
    from statsmodels.stats.api import het_goldfeldquandt, durbin_watson, jarque_bera, linear_rainbow, linear_harvey_collier
    
    print("\nChecking assumption of Homoscedasticity of residuals\n")
    _, pval, a = het_goldfeldquandt(y, x)
    if pval > los:
        print("\tThe residuals are homoscedastic")
    else:
        print("\tThe residuals do not meet this assumption, p-value:",pval)

    sns.scatterplot(np.arange(len(pred)), residuals)
    plt.title("The plot of residuals vs predicted values")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Residuals")
    plt.show()
    
    print("\nChecking assumption of Auto correlation of errors\n")
    r_val = durbin_watson(residuals)
    if (r_val<2.5)|(r_val>1.5) :
        print("\tThe residuals are not auto-correlated")
    else:
        print("\tThe residuals do not meet this assumption, statistic value:",r_val)
    # can make auto-correlation plot here
    
    print("\nChecking assumption of normality of residuals\n")
    _, pval, a, b = jarque_bera(residuals)
    if pval > los:
        print("\tThe residuals distribution is normal")
    else:
        print("\tThe residuals do not meet this assumption, p-value:", pval)
    
    stats.probplot(residuals, plot=plt)
    plt.show()
    
    print("\nChecking assumption of Linearity\n")
    #model = sm.OLS(y, x).fit()
    #_, pval = linear_rainbow(model, 0.5)
    #if pval>0.05:
    #    print("The residuals are homoscedastic")
    #else:
    #    print("The residuals do not meet this assumption")
    sns.regplot(y, pred)
    plt.title("Plot of Predicted vs Observed Values")
    plt.xlabel("Observed Values")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Values")
    plt.show()
    
    print("\nChecking assumption of multicollinearity\n")
    cond = np.linalg.cond(x.values)
    print("\tThe condition number is :", cond)
    if cond> 20:
        print("\tCondition number over 20 are indication of multicollinearity")
        
    print("\n\n")

# can also use below method for the same
#from sklearn.feature_selection import VarianceThreshold

def overfit(data):
    overfit = []
    for i in data.columns:
        perc = (data[i]==0).sum()*100/data.shape[0]
        if perc>99:
            overfit.append(i)
    return overfit

overfit_col = overfit(dummy_auto)
